doc.after: All but one of the major iguana concentrations are either partially or fully protected by the Cuban government 17 Although no captive breeding program exists within Cuba the Centro Nacional de Areas Protegidas the National Center for Protected Areas has suggested it will explore this route in the future 17 In 1985 the Cuban government issued a commemorative peso depicting a Cuban iguana on the head side of the coin in an attempt to raise awareness for this animal 17
